Explanation Document: How Exception Handling WorksPython evaluates code sequentially, but an error can immediately halt execution. Exception handling provides an alternate control flow.The Core Control Flow Blockstry: Contains the code that might cause an error during execution.except: Catches and processes specific errors raised within the try block.else: Runs code only if the try block executes with zero errors.finally: Executes cleanup actions regardless of whether an error occurred or not.
Technical BenefitsApplication Uptime: Prevents complete application failure due to transient faults.Clean Resource Management: Automatically closes files or network connections using the finally block.Targeted Debugging: Catches explicit built-in exception classes instead of hiding unknown system bugs.
